task.summary: spread out repayment graphs with 0 data. make highcharts size height better based on data for criteriatabs and loan repayment graphs, also added repayment % area
fix for charts not redrawing when resized in certain pattern of focusing.
added link to lender page with super graphs to drop down menu
added link to lender page with super graphs to drop down menu
added "Team" page with ability to compare your team's data in a graph.
added Panels to Team. Added another reason to give lender-id to Options,
added better formatting for graphs axis and hover over tooltip
added better formatting for graphs axis and hover over tooltip
not so jumpy with the Alert... move messaging into the panel header and give feedback on how many results are still waiting.
added SharedAPIRequest class, ManualPagedKiva (not used yet), added Compare Teams reference to About and Options, adjusted wording on Options for lender id
fix for weirdness with repayment dates at certain times of day.
stopped using cdn for q. it was slow and never spit back that it wasn't modified... worthless!
async load the bundle, display a "please wait" message since the bundle is 2MB
beefing up server... intro of server fetching loans.
fix for weirdness with repayment dates at certain times of day.
can optionally load from KL server.
text changes on About, Options, and in API notifications, added a 404 response for /feed.svc/rss requests from the old way
is adding loan-related stuff to drop down on /lend ?? shouldn't even be pattern matching for injection. did something change?

kl api can now filter. switched to using kivaloans full class with all of it's goodies. added socket.io client to server so it can update it's list of loans. loans pulled from KL should only be at most 10 seconds stale.
make a reset faster (no distinct, clears the loans). make server faster, store pre-stringified chunks
run server as a cluster... let's hope the cpu usage isn't as crazy as my computer...
